All but one southbound lane of Interstate 275 near the Westshore Boulevard exit was closed on Monday morning after a truck carrying roofing materials overturned, police said. The truck was involved in a crash with multiple cars just north of the Westshore Boulevard exit and overturned, spilling roofing materials onto the interstate, according to Tampa police. One southbound lane of traffic was open as of 7:45 a.m., and the southbound exit to Westshore Boulevard was also closed, police said. Police asked drivers to avoid the area and seek an alternate route. Spectrum Bay News 9 Traffic tweeted a photo of the scene showing a truck on its side.